headline: Oracle and Other AI Stocks Are Spending Too Much Money. These Companies Are Returning Cash in Spades.
summary: Since the end of October, companies returning relatively large amounts of cash to shareholders through dividends and buybacks have seen their stocks outperform others.

headline: Saudia Group Selects GE Aerospace GEnx-1B Engines to Power New 787 Dreamliners
summary: Saudia Group, one of the largest aviation conglomerates in the MENA region, has announced a strategic agreement with GE Aerospace (NYSE: GE) to equip Saudia, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia's national flag carrier, with GEnx-1B engines for its 2023 order of 39 Boeing 787-9 and 787-10 aircraft. headline: Trump Says $270 Billion in Deals Being Signed at US-Saudi Forum
summary: “We’re told that $270 billion in agreements and sales are being signed between dozens of companies, and that’s just happening today,” Trump said Wednesday during a keynote address at the business gathering.  One company named by Trump as entering into a deal is GE Aerospace, which he said would “deliver dozens of new engines.”  The forum comes a day after Trump rolled out the red carpet for Crown Prince Mohammed, also known as MBS, at the White House for a day of dealmaking capped by a dinner with prominent tech, finance and energy executives.
